---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BrandBranchesGrid from '../../components/BrandBranchesGrid.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE, MAIN_PHONE_TEL } from '../../data/branches';

const title = "Smeg Stove Repair | Southern California | Victoria Retro + 60cm Euro";
const description = "Smeg stove repair across SoCal, Victoria retro, Classic, Dolce Stil Novo. 60cm European width signature. $89 dx.";
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/smeg-stove-repair/";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Is Smeg related to Bertazzoni, they're both from Guastalla?",
    a: "Both Smeg and Bertazzoni are headquartered in <b>Guastalla, Emilia-Romagna, Italy</b>, but they are independent Italian family-owned companies with distinct ownership lines. <b>Smeg</b> (Smalterie Metallurgiche Emiliane Guastalla) has been owned by the Bermani family since the 1948 founding and remains independent. <b>Bertazzoni</b> is owned by the Bertazzoni family with stove-making heritage dating to 1882, now in 6th generation. Same region, different families, no corporate overlap. Parts networks are independent, no cross-reference between Smeg and Bertazzoni service. For LA service: Smeg parts distribute through Smeg USA with common service components 5-10 day lead, specialty parts 2-4 weeks from Italian factory. See <a href='/brands/bertazzoni-stove-repair/'>Bertazzoni stove repair</a> for the sibling regional brand."
  },
  {
    q: "What makes the 60cm European-width Smeg different from US-standard stoves?",
    a: "Smeg's signature is the <b>60cm (approximately 24\") European-width freestanding stove</b>, narrower than US-standard 30\" format, making Smeg a natural fit for compact luxury kitchens, West Hollywood condos, Beverly Hills / Santa Monica guest-house kitchens, and secondary-kitchen installs where full 30\"+ format doesn't fit. The narrower cavity has specific service implications: oven racks + bakeware are Euro-format (smaller than US standard), burner spacing is tighter, and some US-spec parts aren't interchangeable. Smeg also offers 90cm (~36\") range format for larger Victoria and Dolce Stil Novo installs. In LA, 60cm Smeg dominates installs, often in design-forward compact kitchens specifically because the Smeg Victoria retro aesthetic in 60cm format is visually distinctive."
  },
  {
    q: "Which Smeg stove lines are most common in LA?",
    a: "<b>Victoria</b> (retro) is the signature Smeg product in LA, 60cm freestanding with 1950s-inspired rounded-corner styling, brass or chrome knob detail, and Smeg's signature pastel color program (Pastel Blue, Pastel Pink, Cream, Red, Black, White, Silver). Victoria in red or Pastel Blue is the iconic Smeg visual. <b>Classic</b> is the mid-luxury conventional Italian-styling line in both 60cm + 90cm. <b>Dolce Stil Novo</b> is the premium modern minimalist line with matte-black + glass detailing, 90cm freestanding flagship. LA Smeg installs concentrate in West Hollywood condos + compact-kitchen luxury (Victoria 60cm volume), Silver Lake + Los Feliz design-forward (Victoria color-program + Dolce Stil Novo modern), Venice + Santa Monica architectural (60cm compact + Dolce Stil Novo premium), Hancock Park + Pasadena heritage-design (Victoria + Classic). WeHo city-page Smeg signal reflects the West Hollywood installation concentration."
  },
  {
    q: "Smeg gas burner not lighting, diagnostic order?",
    a: "Standard European-spec diagnostic: (1) orifice verification, Smeg ships with EU-spec orifices; installs in US sometimes see LP / NG / EU-spec mismatch; orifice swap $180–$280 per burner; (2) spark-module $240–$360 at 8-12 year mark; (3) ignitor tip $180–$280; (4) thermocouple flame-failure $200–$300 (EU safety standard); (5) burner cap seating + port clean $140–$220 per burner; (6) gas valve partial restriction $280–$420; (7) regulator pressure $200–$300. Common 60cm-format specific issue: burner spacing makes port clean more finicky than US 30\" format; we use Smeg-specific burner tools on port-clean service."
  },
  {
    q: "Victoria Pastel Blue (or red) panel damage, replacement process?",
    a: "Smeg's pastel + signature color program is the most iconic element of the Victoria line. Replacement process: (1) document exact color code from interior factory plate; (2) Smeg USA distribution stock check first; (3) currently-produced colors typical 3-5 week lead; (4) legacy or discontinued colors may require 6-10 week Italian factory sourcing (Smeg rotates color catalog generation-by-generation; older Pastel Blue may differ from current Pastel Blue). At intake we confirm color continuity and set honest lead-time expectations. Interior mechanical service runs independently during panel-sourcing wait. Panel prices quoted individually by color + model."
  },
  {
    q: "Oven temperature accuracy on 60cm Victoria ovens, anything specific?",
    a: "60cm oven cavity is smaller than US standard, sensor calibration and cycle-target behavior runs faster than US-format because air volume is smaller. When temperature inaccuracy surfaces: sensor $200–$300, thermostat (analog) $260–$380 on older Victoria, control board $440–$640 on digital Dolce Stil Novo / current-gen Victoria. Convection fan motor $320–$480 on convection-equipped models; thermal fuse $220–$320. Door rope seal $180–$260 per door, seal degradation matters more on 60cm cavity than 30\" because smaller cavity amplifies heat-leak impact on cycle accuracy."
  },
  {
    q: "How does Smeg service cost compare to ILVE or Bertazzoni?",
    a: "Individual parts pricing runs comparable to ILVE / Bertazzoni on core components, 10-15% variance on igniters, thermocouples, sensors, control boards. Smeg's 60cm Euro-format specific parts (racks, specific burners, specific door seals) run slightly more than 30\" format equivalents due to lower production volume. Color-matched panels run 3-10 week lead vs 3-8 week typical on ILVE / Bertazzoni, reflecting Smeg's signature color program which runs batch-production rather than continuous. Diagnostic standard residential $89 waived with repair. Service-life expectation 20+ years typical on well-maintained Smeg with periodic parts servicing. For households in West Hollywood or compact-kitchen LA geographies where 60cm Smeg is the fit, we handle through Smeg USA parts channel with LA-authorized service."
  },
  {
    q: "What does Smeg stove repair cost in LA?",
    a: "Residential diagnostic $89 waived with repair. Typical Smeg bands: orifice swap (per burner) $180–$280; burner cap $140–$220; spark-module $240–$360; ignitor tip $180–$280; thermocouple flame-failure $200–$300; air-mix adjustment $180–$260; gas-line regulator $200–$300; gas valve $280–$420; oven igniter $240–$360; bake element $300–$440; convection fan motor $320–$480; temperature sensor $200–$300; analog thermostat (legacy Victoria) $260–$380; thermal fuse $220–$320; oven door rope seal $180–$260; control board (digital) $440–$640; color-matched panel quoted individually (3-10 week lead). Smeg service runs comparable to ILVE / Bertazzoni on core items with 60cm-format-specific parts at slight premium."
  }
];

const schemaJsons = [
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "LocalBusiness", "@id": canonical + "#business",
    "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair, Smeg Stove Service",
    "image": "https://samedayappliance.repair/images/same-day-appliance-repair.png",
    "url": canonical, "telephone": MAIN_PHONE_TEL, "priceRange": "$$$",
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ]
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Service", "serviceType": "Smeg Stove Repair",
    "provider": { "@id": canonical + "#business" },
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ],
    "description": "Smeg stove repair across Southern California, LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, Riverside. Victoria retro, Classic, Dolce Stil Novo. 60cm European-width freestanding signature + 90cm variants. Pastel + signature color program. Italian Bermani family manufacturer Guastalla since 1948. $89 residential diagnostic waived with repair.",
    "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "priceSpecification": { "@type": "PriceSpecification", "price": "89.00", "priceCurrency": "USD", "description": "Residential diagnostic fee, waived with repair" } }
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": faqs.map(f => ({ "@type": "Question", "name": f.q, "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": f.a } })) },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Brands", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Smeg", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/smeg/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "Smeg Stove Repair", "item": canonical }
    ]
  }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
  <Fragment slot="head-scripts">{schemaJsons.map((schema) => (<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />))}</Fragment>
  <div class="call-banner"><div class="wrap"><span>Smeg stove service? Same-day across all 5 SoCal counties:</span><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="phone-lg">{MAIN_PHONE}</a></div></div>

  <section class="hero"><div class="wrap">
    <div class="crumb"><a href="/">Home</a> › <a href="/brands/">Brands</a> › Smeg › Stove Repair</div>
    <h1>Smeg Stove Repair</h1>
    <p class="lede">Smeg (Smalterie Metallurgiche Emiliane Guastalla) is the Italian Bermani family-owned manufacturer based in Guastalla, Emilia-Romagna, operating since 1948. Smeg's signature is the 60cm (~24") European-width freestanding stove format with the iconic Victoria retro rounded-corner styling, pastel color program (Pastel Blue, Pastel Pink, Cream, Red, Black, White, Silver), and brass / chrome knob detail. Distinct from Bertazzoni (same Guastalla region, different family, different product positioning). Classic and Dolce Stil Novo lines extend Smeg's offering beyond the signature Victoria retro into mid-luxury conventional + premium modern formats. In LA, Smeg concentrates in West Hollywood condos, Silver Lake + Los Feliz design-forward kitchens, Venice + Santa Monica architectural compact installs, Hancock Park + Pasadena heritage-design. Parts through Smeg USA 5-10 day typical; Italian-factory specialty parts 2-4 weeks; color-matched panels 3-10 weeks depending on color. Same-day dispatch, $89 residential diagnostic waived with the repair.</p>
    <div class="hero-cta"><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="btn btn-primary">Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a><a href="#book" class="btn btn-ghost">Request a Visit</a></div>
    <ul class="hero-facts">
      <li><b>Bermani family Italian Guastalla since 1948</b>, independent</li>
      <li><b>60cm European-width signature</b>, compact-kitchen luxury fit</li>
      <li><b>Victoria retro + Classic + Dolce Stil Novo</b>, three-line lineup</li>
      <li><b>$89 residential diagnostic</b>, waived when you authorize the repair</li>
    </ul>
  </div></section>

  <BrandBranchesGrid />

  <section class="trust-bar"><div class="wrap"><span>BHGS #A49573 · Insured</span><span>Same-day in 5 SoCal counties</span><span>Residential diagnostic $89 · waived with repair</span></div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Smeg in LA, 60cm Euro-format as compact-luxury signature</h2>
    <p>Smeg occupies a specific LA market position because of the 60cm European-width format. Most US luxury stoves (Viking / Wolf / Thermador / Bertazzoni / ILVE) start at 30" format and scale up to 48" or 60". Smeg starts at 60cm (~24") and extends to 90cm (~36"), meaning Smeg fits kitchens that US-format stoves don't, particularly compact LA condos, guest-house kitchens, secondary-kitchen spaces, and design-forward compact primary kitchens where the 60cm format + Victoria retro aesthetic is a deliberate design choice. The WeHo (West Hollywood) city-page Smeg signal reflects this, WeHo condo installs concentrate Smeg because 60cm fits where 30"+ doesn't, and Victoria styling matches WeHo design sensibility.</p>
    <p>Our LA Smeg service geography tracks the installed-base concentration. West Hollywood condo primary + secondary kitchens with 60cm Victoria; Silver Lake + Los Feliz design-district homes with Victoria color-program + occasional Dolce Stil Novo premium; Venice + Santa Monica architectural compact kitchens; Hancock Park + Larchmont + Pasadena heritage-design households where Victoria or Classic at 60cm fits an older kitchen footprint; Bel Air + Beverly Hills guest-house / compact secondary kitchens with 60cm Smeg as design choice. Parts through Smeg USA network; specialty or color-matched components occasionally run 6-10 week Italian-factory source.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Smeg stove failures our techs see most often</h2>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Gas burner no-light, orifice / spark / thermocouple</h3><p>EU-spec parts standard. Orifice $180–$280 per burner; spark $240–$360; thermocouple $200–$300.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>60cm oven temperature drift</h3><p>Smaller cavity amplifies sensor impact. Sensor $200–$300; analog thermostat (legacy) $260–$380; digital control board $440–$640.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Pastel / color panel exterior damage</h3><p>Italian factory sourcing 3-10 week lead depending on color. Quoted individually.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Oven door rope seal degradation</h3><p>60cm cavity amplifies seal impact. Seal $180–$260 per door.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Convection fan motor</h3><p>Motor $320–$480 on convection-equipped Classic / Dolce Stil Novo.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Victoria brass / chrome knob trim</h3><p>Heat-cycle stress on knob trim. Replacement hardware 5-10 day lead; installation $140–$220.</p></div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Smeg stove product lines we service</h2>
    <div class="model-grid">
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Victoria (retro signature)</h3><p>60cm freestanding. Rounded-corner 1950s-inspired. Brass / chrome knob detail. Pastel + signature color program.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Classic line</h3><p>Mid-luxury conventional Italian styling. 60cm + 90cm. Standard stainless or color trim.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Dolce Stil Novo (premium modern)</h3><p>Matte-black + glass detailing. 90cm freestanding flagship. Premium minimalist aesthetic.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>60cm Euro-format signature</h3><p>~24" width. Fits compact kitchens + condos + guest-house spaces where 30"+ doesn't.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Pastel color program</h3><p>Pastel Blue, Pastel Pink, Cream, Red, Black, White, Silver. Iconic Smeg colors on Victoria line.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>90cm wider variants</h3><p>Classic and Dolce Stil Novo extend to 90cm (~36"). Larger-kitchen luxury installs.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Smeg vs Bertazzoni vs ILVE, Italian family brands</h2>
    <p>Three Italian family-owned stove brands with distinct family + regional identity.</p>
    <p><b>Smeg (this page)</b>, Bermani family Guastalla since 1948, 60cm European-width signature, Victoria retro iconography, pastel color program.</p>
    <p><b>Bertazzoni</b>, Bertazzoni family Guastalla (same region) since 1882, 6th generation, Professional Series pro-style freestanding, 60+ enamel colors. See <a href="/brands/bertazzoni-stove-repair/">Bertazzoni stove repair</a>.</p>
    <p><b>ILVE</b>, Treviso family (Veneto, different region) since 1975, Majestic III flagship, 60+ colors + five knob-trim material options. See <a href="/brands/ilve-stove-repair/">ILVE stove repair</a>.</p>
    <p>Choice drivers: Smeg for 60cm compact-kitchen fit + Victoria retro iconography; Bertazzoni for Professional pro-style + 6th-generation heritage; ILVE for widest flexibility + Majestic III full-lineup.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>What Smeg stove repair typically costs</h2>
    <table class="price-table">
      <tr><th>Service</th><th>Typical Range</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Residential diagnostic</td><td>$89</td><td>Waived with repair</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Orifice swap (per burner)</td><td>$180 – $280</td><td>EU / LP / NG mismatch</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Burner cap replacement</td><td>$140 – $220</td><td>Per burner</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Spark-module ignition</td><td>$240 – $360</td><td>8-12 year service</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Ignitor tip clean / replace</td><td>$180 – $280</td><td>Carbon / electrode wear</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Thermocouple flame-failure</td><td>$200 – $300</td><td>EU safety spec</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Gas-line regulator</td><td>$200 – $300</td><td>Pressure stability</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Gas valve swap</td><td>$280 – $420</td><td>Stuck / restricted</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Oven igniter</td><td>$240 – $360</td><td>Pro-range oven-side</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Bake element</td><td>$300 – $440</td><td>Electric oven-side</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Convection fan motor</td><td>$320 – $480</td><td>Convection variants</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Temperature sensor</td><td>$200 – $300</td><td>Oven accuracy</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Analog thermostat (legacy Victoria)</td><td>$260 – $380</td><td>Mechanical-dial models</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Thermal fuse / high-limit</td><td>$220 – $320</td><td>Safety cutout</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Oven door rope seal</td><td>$180 – $260</td><td>Per door</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Control board (digital)</td><td>$440 – $640</td><td>Dolce Stil Novo / current Victoria</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Victoria knob / trim</td><td>$140 – $220</td><td>Installation labor</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Color-matched panel</td><td>Quoted individually</td><td>3-10 week lead by color</td></tr>
    </table>
    <p class="small">Related: <a href="/brands/smeg/">Smeg brand hub</a> · <a href="/brands/bertazzoni-stove-repair/">Bertazzoni stove repair</a> · <a href="/brands/ilve-stove-repair/">ILVE stove repair</a> · <a href="/west-hollywood/">West Hollywood service</a>.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Service areas, where our Smeg stove calls come from</h2>
    <div class="area-grid">
      <div><h4>West Hollywood (volume)</h4><p><a href="/west-hollywood/">West Hollywood</a> · Beverly Grove · Sunset Strip condos</p></div>
      <div><h4>Silver Lake + Los Feliz</h4><p>Silver Lake · Los Feliz · Echo Park</p></div>
      <div><h4>Venice + Santa Monica</h4><p>Venice · Santa Monica · Mar Vista</p></div>
      <div><h4>Hancock Park + Larchmont</h4><p>Hancock Park · Larchmont · Windsor Square</p></div>
      <div><h4>Pasadena + South Pasadena</h4><p><a href="/pasadena/">Pasadena</a> · South Pasadena · Altadena</p></div>
      <div><h4>Bel Air + Beverly Hills guest-house</h4><p><a href="/beverly-hills/">Beverly Hills</a> · Bel Air · compact secondary kitchens</p></div>
    </div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Related Smeg and Italian-family pages</h2>
    <ul class="related-links">
      <li><a href="/brands/smeg/">Smeg brand hub →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/brands/smeg-repair/">Smeg repair (all appliances) →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/brands/bertazzoni-stove-repair/">Bertazzoni stove repair →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/brands/ilve-stove-repair/">ILVE stove repair →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/brands/fulgor-milano-stove-repair/">Fulgor Milano stove repair →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/west-hollywood/">West Hollywood service area →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/services/stove-repair/">Stove repair (service hub) →</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Smeg stove repair, frequently asked</h2>
    {faqs.map(f => (<details class="faq"><summary>{f.q}</summary><p set:html={f.a}></p></details>))}
  </div></section>

  <section id="book" class="cta-bottom"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Smeg stove service? Call the branch closest to your home.</h2>
    <p>Same-day appliance repair across Los Angeles, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, and Riverside counties. Residential diagnostic $89, waived with repair.</p>
  </div></section>
  <a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="float-call" aria-label="Call now">☎ Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a>
</Layout>

<style>
  :root { --red: #C8102E; --black: #0a0a0a; --gray: #f5f5f5; --border: #e2e2e2; --text: #1a1a1a; --muted: #6b6b6b; }
  body { color: var(--text); } .wrap { max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px; } .wrap.narrow { max-width: 820px; }
  h1 { font-size: 2.4rem; line-height: 1.15; margin: 12px 0 20px; color: var(--black); }
  h2 { font-size: 1.8rem; margin: 0 0 16px; color: var(--black); }
  h3 { font-size: 1.2rem; margin: 0 0 10px; color: var(--black); }
  h4 { font-size: 1.02rem; margin: 0 0 6px; color: var(--black); }
  p { line-height: 1.65; margin: 0 0 14px; }
  .call-banner { background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 10px 0; }
  .call-banner .wrap { display:flex; gap: 14px; align-items: center; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .call-banner .phone-lg { color:#fff; font-weight: 800; text-decoration: underline; font-size: 1.05rem; }
  .hero { background: var(--black); color: #fff; padding: 42px 0 56px; } .hero h1 { color: #fff; }
  .hero .lede { font-size: 1.06rem; color: #d7d7d7; max-width: 680px; }
  .hero .crumb { color: #9a9a9a; font-size: 0.85rem; margin-bottom: 6px; } .hero .crumb a { color: #c9c9c9; text-decoration: none; }
  .hero-cta { display: flex; gap: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin: 18px 0 24px; }
  .btn { display: inline-block; padding: 12px 20px; border-radius: 4px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 700; }
  .btn-primary { background: var(--red); color: #fff; } .btn-ghost { background: transparent; color: #fff; border: 1px solid #fff; }
  .hero-facts { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; color: #c9c9c9; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  .hero-facts li { padding: 6px 0; border-top: 1px solid #222; } .hero-facts li:first-child { border-top: 0; }
  .trust-bar { background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 14px 0; }
  .trust-bar .wrap { display: flex; gap: 28px; flex-wrap: wrap; justify-content: center; font-size: 0.95rem; font-weight: 600; }
  .section { padding: 56px 0; } .section.alt { background: var(--gray); }
  .model-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap: 20px; margin-top: 24px; }
  .model-card { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 20px; border-radius: 6px; }
  .section.alt .model-card { background: #fff; }
  .fail-block { background: #fff; border-left: 3px solid var(--red); padding: 20px 22px; margin: 16px 0; }
  .price-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 14px; background: #fff; }
  .price-table th, .price-table td { text-align: left; padding: 11px 12px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .price-table th { background: var(--black); color: #fff; font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  .small { color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.92rem; margin-top: 12px; }
  .area-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr)); gap: 18px; }
  .area-grid > div { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 16px; border-radius: 6px; }
  .related-links { list-style: none; padding: 0; } .related-links li { padding: 10px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .related-links a { color: var(--red); font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; } .related-links a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
  .faq { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 12px 16px; margin-bottom: 8px; border-radius: 4px; }
  .faq summary { font-weight: 700; cursor: pointer; padding: 4px 0; } .faq p { margin: 8px 0 0; }
  .cta-bottom { background: var(--black); color: #fff; padding: 48px 0; } .cta-bottom h2 { color: #fff; } .cta-bottom p { color: #c9c9c9; }
  .float-call { position: fixed; bottom: 18px; right: 18px; background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 14px 18px; border-radius: 40px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 700; box-shadow: 0 6px 18px rgba(0,0,0,0.28); z-index: 50; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  @media (max-width: 820px) { h1 { font-size: 1.9rem; } h2 { font-size: 1.45rem; } .float-call { padding: 11px 14px; font-size: 0.88rem; } .trust-bar .wrap { gap: 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; } }
</style>
